  "prompt": "What are some great online resources for learning the Go (Golang) programming language?",
  "response": "Here are some excellent online resources for learning Go (Golang):\n\n1. Official Resources\n- Go's Official Documentation (go.dev)\n- Go Tour (tour.golang.org) - Interactive tutorial\n- Go Standard Library Documentation\n- Go Playground (play.golang.org)\n\n2. Online Courses\n- Udemy: Go Programming Language\n- Coursera: Programming with Google Go Specialization\n- Pluralsight Go Courses\n- LinkedIn Learning Go Tutorials\n\n3. Free Online Tutorials/Websites\n- GoByExample.com\n- TutorialEdge.net Go Tutorial\n- Codecademy Go Course\n- golangbot.com\n\n4. YouTube Channels\n- Tech With Tim\n- Traversy Media\n- Sentdex\n- freeCodeCamp.org Go tutorials\n\n5. Interactive Learning Platforms\n- Exercism.io (Go track)\n- LeetCode Go problems\n- HackerRank Go challenges\n\n6. GitHub Resources\n- Awesome Go (curated list of Go resources)\n- Go GitHub repositories\n- Open-source Go projects\n\n7. Books (with online resources)\n- \"The Go Programming Language\" by Alan Donovan\n- \"Learning Go\" by Jon Bodner\n- Many books offer free online chapters/samples\n\nThese resources cover various skill levels from beginner to advanced.",
